Ad Text:
Who are we?

UpGuard’s mission is to make life easier for security teams. We meticulously create robust solutions that enable our customers to identify, assess, and remediate cybersecurity risk across their attack surface, vendor ecosystem, workforce, and trust relationships. Our integrated cyber risk posture management platform combines comprehensive security ratings, instant risk assessments, templated security questionnaires, threat intelligence capabilities, and agentic AI to give organizations a holistic view of their risk surface.

Our Product team at UpGuard comprises of our Product Management, Product Support, Engineering, Design, Data Leaks Detection, and Third Party Risk Management Services. Our Product team’s vision is to become the leader in the Cyber VRM category by providing a best-in-class SaaS platform for organizations to manage their third-party risk and external attack surface. Our purpose as a Product team is simply to build a product that enables this. We aim to build a product that users love and come to rely on, and one that regularly and consistently improves.

Where does this role fit in? 

We’re looking for a Senior Data Scientist to lead the evolution of our scoring algorithms, provide data-driven insights to our product squads, and help shape how AI is applied across our products. This role bridges analytics, data science, and applied AI, helping turn complex security data into actionable, trustworthy intelligence.

What will you do?

Own the design, evolution, and validation of UpGuard’s scoring algorithms across all surfaces - Vendor, Attack Surface, Breach, and User Risk.
Develop statistical and ML models that translate raw security data into meaningful, calibrated scores.
Measure and improve score accuracy, stability, and interpretability.
Work with engineers to deploy and monitor models in production environments.
Partner with PMs and designers to define success metrics and measure product outcomes.
Conduct in-depth analyses of adoption, engagement, and retention to guide roadmap priorities.
Build reusable datasets, dashboards, and frameworks for self-serve analytics.
Establish best practices for experimentation and data-driven decision making across squads.
Collaborate with squads building AI-powered features, from automated vendor assessments to breach intelligence and risk summarization.
Prototype and evaluate new AI/ML techniques (including LLMs, embeddings, and anomaly detection).
Define standards for safe, efficient AI usage, including model evaluation and prompt testing.
What will you bring?

5+ years of experience applying quantitative methods, ideally within a high-growth company, with practical exposure to risk modelling and uncertainty analysis.
Advanced analytics expertise: Proven track record in building complex statistical or actuarial models (e.g., 5+ years of experience in data science, AI, actuarial science, or similar).
AI/ML proficiency: Hands-on experience implementing machine learning approaches (regression, classification, ensemble methods, NLP, deep learning, etc.) in real-world applications.
Strong statistical foundations: Deep understanding of regression analysis, probability theory, and inferential statistics to accurately model risk.
Engineering background: Comfortable working with Go, Python and relational and columnar databases (we use Postgres and BigQuery)
Collaborative mindset: Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills to align with product managers, engineers, and other cross-functional teams.
Leadership and ownership: Ability to define a vision, set clear objectives, and drive results in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
What will give you an edge?

Familiarity with or enthusiasm for cybersecurity, cyber risk management, or related fields is highly desirable.
Domain experience in actuarial science, credit risk, and threat intelligence
What's in it for you?

Monthly Lifestyle subsidy: Use this for financial, physical, and mental well-being 
WFH set-up allowance: To ensure you have the right environment to work in, we will help you get set up within your first 3 months at UpGuard 
$1500 USD annual Learning & Development allowance: To support your career development, all team members will be able to expense development opportunities against this allowance 
Annual leave: PTO plus two additional UpGuardian leave days to give you time to recharge your batteries.
18 weeks paid Parental Leave: Irrespective of parenting role
Personal Leave Allowance: This includes sick & carer’s leave 
Fully remote working environment: While we have physical offices in Sydney & Hobart, we do not mandate compulsory attendance
Top-spec hardware: All team members will be provided with top-spec laptops for their role 
Generative AI subsidy: UpGuard provides paid subscriptions for all team members to access generative AI tools to support their work

Job Title: Senior Data & Analytics Consultant - Databricks / Microsoft Fabric
Ad Text:
Senior Data & Analytics Consultant – Databricks / Microsoft Fabric

D2i Consulting Pty Ltd
Melbourne VIC (Hybrid)
Full-Time | Senior Consulting | Data & AI Solutions

D2i is a high-growth Data & Analytics consultancy helping organisations modernise their data platforms, adopt AI-driven insights, and unlock transformational business value. We are now seeking a Senior Data & Analytics Consultant with strong hands-on experience in Databricks and/or Microsoft Fabric, combined with the consulting capability to lead delivery, shape solutions, and engage effectively with senior business stakeholders.

This role is ideal for an experienced data professional who is ready to step into a client-facing, solution-driven consulting role with ownership of delivery outcomes and the opportunity to influence strategy and architecture.

About the Role

As a Senior Data & Analytics Consultant, you will lead key workstreams within modern data platform, analytics, and engineering engagements. You’ll work directly with business and technical stakeholders to understand their needs, define solutions, and deliver high-quality data products across Databricks, Fabric, and Azure.

You will shape data strategies, design modern data architectures, drive best practices, and mentor junior team members—all while ensuring client outcomes are met with high quality and professionalism.

Key Responsibilities
Solution Design & Technical Leadership

Lead the design of modern data solutions using Databricks, Microsoft Fabric, and Azure analytics services.

Architect ingestion, transformation, and modelling layers aligned to best practices in ELT, medallion architecture, and scalable cloud design.

Translate business problems into technical designs, working alongside architects and client stakeholders.

Data Engineering & Platform Delivery

Develop high-quality pipelines and transformations using PySpark, SQL, Databricks notebooks, Fabric Data Engineering, and Azure Data Factory.

Build robust data models and refined layers suitable for analytics, finance reporting, operational dashboards, and predictive use cases.

Apply mature engineering practices including CI/CD, testing frameworks, version control, and development standards.

Advanced Analytics & Enablement

Contribute to advisory work including AI readiness assessments, data platform modernisation strategies, and roadmap development.

Support Power BI enablement and data product preparation where required.

Stakeholder Engagement & Consulting

Facilitate workshops and discovery sessions with technical, business, and executive stakeholders.

Communicate complex technical concepts in business-friendly language.

Provide guidance, recommendations, and insights to drive client decision-making.

Delivery Ownership & Leadership

Lead delivery of end-to-end workstreams with accountability for outcomes, timelines, and quality.

Mentor mid-level and junior consultants to uplift capability within the team.

Prepare clear documentation, solution outlines, architectural notes, and handover materials.

About You

You are an experienced data consultant (or a senior engineer ready to step up) who can combine strong hands-on delivery with strategic thinking and excellent client engagement.

You will bring:

5–8+ years’ experience in data engineering, analytics delivery, or data platform consulting.

Strong capability in Databricks and/or Microsoft Fabric, including PySpark, SQL, notebooks, orchestration, and performance optimisation.

Strong understanding of Dimensional Modelling, ELT patterns, medallion architecture, and modern data warehousing.

Experience designing or delivering cloud data platforms on Azure.

Confident stakeholder engagement skills, including workshops, presentations, and solution walkthroughs.

Ability to work independently, guide others, and take ownership of client outcomes.

Nice to Have

Experience with SAP, enterprise ERP data structures, or large-scale migration projects.

Power BI capability (data models, DAX, dashboard design).

Prior consulting or professional services experience.

Requirements

Must have full Australian working rights.

Availability to commence within 2–4 weeks (preferred but flexible).

Strong communication and presentation skills.

Ability to operate in a hybrid agile delivery model with autonomy.

Why Join D2i?

Work on cutting-edge Data & AI transformation projects across enterprise and government clients.

Senior-level ownership with opportunities to influence architecture and delivery approach.

Hybrid working model with flexibility.

Collaborative culture with strong technical leadership and support.

Opportunity to mentor consultants and shape project outcomes.

Leave benefits, birthday perks, and transport allowances.
Onsite parking and easy access to public transport.
This is a fantastic opportunity for someone who thrives at the intersection of finance, analytics, and business partnering, with the chance to make a real impact on strategic growth.

Job Title: General Manager, Policy and Analysis Branch, Net Zero Economy Authority
Company: Department of the Prime Minister and Cabinet
Ad Text:
Step into a pivotal leadership role as General Manager, Policy and Analysis with the Net Zero Economy Authority, where you’ll drive national policy and data strategy at the forefront of Australia’s economic and social transformation. This is your opportunity to shape the Authority’s policy agenda, lead high-performing teams, and deliver evidence-based insights that support workers, communities, and industries through the net zero transition. You’ll collaborate with senior officials, industry, and regional leaders, ensuring decisions are informed by robust analysis and innovative thinking. If you’re a strategic, values-driven leader with a passion for public sector impact and a commitment to building a better future, this high-profile executive position offers the chance to make a lasting difference.

Flexibility arrangements

Flexible work is a broad term used to describe a variety of different arrangements about how, when and where work is performed. The authority supports mutually beneficial flexible work arrangements which suit operational requirements. Arrangements may be consistent and regular, such as part time work, working from home a couple of days each week or remotely from another location; or more ad hoc such as varying work attendance times or occasional home based work. Consideration is given to all flexible work requests, approval is not limited to an employee’s classification level or caring responsibilities.

Eligibility

This role is being advertised as both ongoing and non-ongoing. The role may be offered as either ongoing or non-ongoing subject to business needs and/or candidate preference. Where a non-ongoing position is offered, the role will be filled as a specified term vacancy for an initial period of up to 12 months.
Under section 22(8) of the Public Service Act 1999, employees must be Australian citizens to be employed in the Australian Public Service (APS) unless the Agency Head has agreed otherwise, in writing. At NZEA (PM&C) to be eligible for this position you should be an Australian Citizen at the closing date of application, unless exceptional circumstances apply (see FAQs in the candidate information pack for more details).
Successful applicants will be required to undergo the process to obtain and maintain, or continue to hold the required security clearance level for the role as indicated. All NZEA staff are required to have a minimum baseline security clearance prior to commencement.
Successful applicants will be assessed through our pre-employment screening checks, including a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check, and will normally be subject to a six-month probation period if new to the APS, or if they have not yet completed their probation period elsewhere in the APS.

How to apply

If this sounds like the opportunity you are looking for, submit an online application through the Apply link by Sunday, 18 January 2026 at 11:30pm AEDT.

Company: Talent – Specialists in tech, transformation & beyond
Ad Text:
Join one of Australia's leading national retailers as an AI/ML Platform Engineering Manager, where you will play a pivotal role in shaping and scaling the organisation's next-generation machine learning capabilities. This is a permanent leadership opportunity overseeing a high-performing team of six engineers and driving end-to-end ownership of the AI/ML platform.

About the Role

In this role, you will lead the design, development, and delivery of critical AI/ML platform components supporting enterprise-wide machine learning initiatives. You will partner closely with data scientists, ML engineers, software developers, and platform teams to translate business needs into scalable and secure platform capabilities.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the architecture and development of AI/ML platform components including model training environments, feature stores, model registries, deployment pipelines, and monitoring frameworks.
Manage end-to-end delivery of platform enhancements, ensuring scalability, reliability, and high performance across all ML workloads.
Collaborate cross-functionally with technical and non-technical stakeholders to gather requirements and enable seamless delivery of AI/ML solutions.
Implement and champion best practices in MLOps, including model versioning, lifecycle management, CI/CD, observability, and platform security.
Drive continuous improvement by integrating new tools, frameworks, and automation to streamline and accelerate ML workflows.
Oversee platform reliability, incident response, operational support, and capacity planning to maintain enterprise-grade availability.
Ensure all platform capabilities adhere to organisational data governance, security standards, and relevant regulatory requirements.
Provide regular reporting, insights, and strategic recommendations to senior leadership on platform performance, risks, and future opportunities.


About You

You are a technical leader with a passion for building robust, scalable AI/ML platforms and empowering teams to deliver impactful machine learning outcomes. You thrive in a fast-paced, collaborative environment and bring deep experience in MLOps, automation, and cloud-native engineering.

What's on Offer

Permanent leadership role in a high-growth AI/ML environment
Opportunity to shape a major retailer's enterprise ML ecosystem
Lead and develop a team of six talented engineers
Competitive salary, benefits, and long-term career pathways

For more information contact Melissa Haddad at melissa.haddad@talentinternational.com

Senior Data Engineer

We’re looking for a Senior Data Engineer who thrives at the intersection of real-time data, platforms, and modern analytics. This is a hands-on role for someone who wants to architect, scale, and optimise streaming platforms that power decision-making, analytics, and AI.

If you live and breathe event-driven architecture, love working with Microsoft Fabric and Azure, and are excited by building resilient, near real-time systems — this role is for you.

What you’ll be doing

You will play a key role in building and evolving the real-time data ecosystem, helping the business turn streaming data into actionable insights.

Design, build and optimise scalable, production-grade data pipelines using Microsoft Fabric and Azure services.
Develop robust integrations between databases, APIs, Kafka, etc to ensure high-quality, real-time data flow.
Implement streaming solutions using frameworks such as Kafka Streams, Apache Flink, and Spark Streaming.
Own the performance and reliability of the data pipelines — proactively monitoring, troubleshooting and tuning for scale and low latency.
Champion data governance, quality, and compliance while protecting data privacy and security.
Collaborate closely with Data Architects, Analysts and Project teams to design modern data platforms.
Drive continuous improvement across architecture, tooling and development standards.
Mentor junior data engineers
Produce and maintain technical documentation to ensure platform durability and knowledge sharing.
Support the development of machine learning pipelines and AI use-cases by delivering reliable, streaming data foundations.
What you'll bring

Experience with Microsoft Fabric
Experience with Power BI, Azure Data Factory, Azure Data Lake, Azure Data Warehouse, SQL Server, Python
Good understanding of Azure DevOps & CI/CD pipelines
Strong understanding of distributed systems, event-driven architecture and microservices.
Hands-on experience in building or supporting machine learning pipelines or AI workflows.
Solid data architecture fundamentals and performance optimisation experience.
Tertiary qualification (ideally Master’s level) in Computer Science, Engineering, or related field.
Power BI certification or Microsoft data engineering certifications.
If it sounds like a role you'd be a good fit for, please apply now!

Job Title: Senior Lecturer in International Business or Strategic Management
Ad Text:
Classification: Academic Level C 
Salary package: $142,446 - $158,323 per annum plus 17% superannuation  
Terms: Full time, Continuing

Position Description: PD_Senior Lecturer in IB and Strategic Management_2025

Position overview 

The Research School of Management in the ANU College of Business and Economics aims to create and share management knowledge that makes a difference to organisations and society. Nine academics with affiliations to our School are listed among the 2025 Stanford/Elsevier Top 2% Scientists.

To continue the current growth trajectory, we are seeking to recruit a Senior Lecturer (Level C) in the field of International Business or Strategic Management. The successful applicant will conduct research of international standing and actively contribute to undergraduate and postgraduate teaching in the School. They will have a strong work ethic, a practical approach, and be passionate about the quality of their work. The successful applicant will join a strong team of academics who publish in top international journals and hold external competitive grants. The School and College provide an excellent research environment, including favourable teaching load and internal research support. 

The position is open to international applicants. The successful applicant must be available to commence work in Canberra (Australia) by mid-2026. The successful applicant will be offered relocation assistance as per ANU Policy. 

We have a strong equal opportunity culture. We encourage all applicants particularly, female, Aboriginal or Torres Strait Islander applicants. 

Enquiries: Professor Lin Cui at lin.cui@anu.edu.au.   

College overview 

The Australian National University (ANU) is one of the world’s great universities, ranking 32nd in the 2026 QS World University Rankings. The Research School of Management sits within the ANU College of Business and Economics. The College educates the next generation of business leaders, professional economists and academics. Our graduates have the knowledge and skills to lead organisations, design public policy, and research the big issues of business and economy.

Located in the national capital, we engage deeply with the business and policy communities. Our academics lead public debate on the critical issues of our time through their research, which is both long term and strategic in focus. Our internationally diverse student body is evenly divided between undergraduate and postgraduate study, and we have a large doctoral program. Our alumni are found in the world's leading companies, policy agencies and universities. 

We strongly believe that the way in which we operate is defined by our Values and Behaviours and encourage you to apply if you are looking for a workplace that encourages respect, collegiality and excellence. 

The University actively encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people. For more information on employment opportunities, contact our Indigenous Employment Consultant on indigenous.employment@anu.edu.au.

ANU values diversity and inclusion and believes employment opportunities must not be limited by socio-economic background, race, religion or gender. For more information about staff equity at ANU, visit https://services.anu.edu.au/business-units/human-resources-division/equity-and-diversity 

Application information 

In order to apply for this role please make sure that you upload the following documents: 

A statement (3 pages max) addressing each of the selection criteria
A current curriculum vitae (CV) which includes the names and contact details of at least three referees (preferably including a current or previous supervisor). If your CV does not include referees you can provide these online when prompted in the application form.  

Applications that do not address the selection criteria may not be considered for the position. 

Please note: The successful candidate will be required to undergo a background check during the recruitment process.  An offer of employment is conditional on satisfactory results.  

Closing Date: Thursday, 15 January 2026, 11.55pm (AEST)
